snippet.textDisplay: How ironic is it that I am a punjabi muslim from punjab Pakistan sitting in America and listening to a punjabi song sang by sikh people of india. Its a small world; we must not forget who we are and where we come from. We are one people no matter where we live Pakistan, india or elsewhere, no need for dividing between. Mein punjabi waan; buhat acha gana eana ne gaya wee; Allah eana parawan da palla kare, maza aa gaya.
